Totaljobs Group is a collection of six online job boards in the United Kingdom, owned by Axel Springer SE via its subsidiary StepStone. Head quartered at the Blue Fin building, London, the Group has offices in Birmingham, Cardiff, Leeds, Nottingham and Glasgow.
Founded in 1999 by publisher Reed Elsevier with the launch of totaljobs.com (now totaljobs), in April 2012 it was purchased as part of a Â£110M deal by StepStone, a subsidiary of Axel Springer Digital Classifieds. The Group currently employs around 400 people.
